	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=142109><span id= >NecromasterZ</span></a><br><span id=notbold>4 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Hey guys, just read your posts about leveling solo at 50+<br><br>Here's my recommendation.&nbsp;&nbsp;Don't solo.  Try to get groups and make a few more friends it'll help you out in the long run.<br><br>However.  If you want to solo for the better xp,  (I actually did solo through 54) Here's what I did and I'm going to do.  Since 50 i've been soloing Cindreela the guardian of the portal to fear in the Feerot zone.<br><br>Go through the spectre tunnel in the SW portion of Feerot.  The best way i've found to get through here unscathed is to charm one spec and have him attack another to clear the way, but I usually try to sneak through.  The specs are tougher than the ones in Oasis, and they can see invis and invis undead too so it's tough.<br><br>Cindy is not real powerfull.  You just have to be able to resist her fear spell.  The first time you kill her she'll have a pet.  Just root her pet, then dark/fear cindy while your pet kills her.  Then finish off the pet.  After that it's cake as long as you lay the smack down on Cindy before she summons her pet.  If you do get feared, the fear path will generally send you back through the spec cave but generally it will wear off before you get into trouble.<br><br>Bonus for soloing on Cindy is there are Dry Bones Skeletons wandering around there so you can always farm bone chips while your there.  She still cons dark blue to me at 54 but she's a massive overcon and can be killed easily at 50.  Great xp up until 55.<br>--------------------------------------------------<br>After 55 I'll be heading to Skyfire to solo wyverns and such.  I haven't had any experience soloing here but from talk with fellow necros that's what everyone else does when they can't find a group.<br><br>From talking with everyone.  90% of the necro population agrees that finding a group post 50 in Seb or Kael or Chardok is the best way to go though.<br><br>Just one other plug.  I've set up a small home on the web for Necromancers at <br><br><a href="http://www.necromasterz.com" target=_new>http://www.necromasterz.com</a><br><br>As of right now it's up and running.  It has links and news sections as well as a place to submit and view screenshots, soon I will have my own Necromancer section up with info on soloing help, group play and other such topics so stop by, take a look, and email any suggestions such as new links you'd like added, or any info you'd like to see me post and i'll put it up right away.<br><br>My email address is on the bottom of the page.<br><br>Thanks,<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed Feb  6 15:56:12 2002</em></p>&nbsp;<br>Suuen Orlayter<br>54th DE Necromancer<br>Erollisi Marr </td></td></tr>
