	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=117714><span id=Scholar>Neverwinter</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>59 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.04]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Ok here is what i know on the subject from experience...<br><br>If a mob is comming at you (ie you are kiting it) it will definately not take full damage.&nbsp;&nbsp;It's slighty more than half normal, i've heard 66% from a number of people.<br><br>If you are fear kiting a mob it will take 100% damage.  Apparently Verant though they should nerf druids and not necros lol.<br><br>If a mob is rooted and dotted (root n' rot) it will still take 100% damage. Of course getting druid root to actually stick ... =P<br><br>Hope this clears things up a little.<br><br>Neverwinter</p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
